oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cable cutter product model, 1963 December 6
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Product model of a cable cutter used in the 1964 catalog for Sherman and Reilly, Inc., of Chattanooga, Tennessee. Text on cover reads, "CABLE CUTTER. Cam type cable cutter provides smooth, even cut on all types of cable, even wire rope up to 1 1/4" in diameter. Unique wrench type adjustment on hardended steel blade provides long, continuous, positive action. A rugged tool with extra long handle for cutting the toughest cable with ease. Cutter mounted on wood based equipped with handle and rollers for portability."
